definition.value: Cardiac valve which has as its parts the right anterior, left anterior and posterior cusps, attached to the fibrous ring of pulmonary valve.
The cerebral crus is the most anterior portion of the midbrain which consists of a massive band of nerve fibers originating primarily from the cerebral cortex.

label.value: Left anterior cusp of pulmonary valve

definition.value: Organ component which is attached to the semilunar fibrous scallop of pulmonary valve anulus.

label.value: Right anterior cusp of pulmonary valve
